stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (MELTDOWN vs TANTRUM \(Know the Difference\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 686.0 Td (TANTRUM \(goal-directed\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 670.0 Td (- Child wants something specific) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.0 Td (- Watches for your reaction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.0 Td (- Stops when they get what they want \(or realize they won't\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.0 Td (- Can be redirected) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 610.0 Td (MELTDOWN \(nervous system overload\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 594.0 Td (- Caused by sensory/emotional overwhelm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 580.0 Td (- NOT within the child's control) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 566.0 Td (- Cannot be reasoned with during it) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.0 Td (- Needs safety and time to pass) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 524.2 Td (DURING A MELTDOWN:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.2 Td (  1. Ensure safety \(move dangerous objects, create space\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.2 Td (  2. Reduce sensory input \(lights down, people back, quiet voice\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.2 Td (  3. Don't talk too much \(processing is overloaded\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.2 Td (  4. Offer comfort items \(blanket, headphones, chewy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.2 Td (  5. Wait. Be calm. Be present. It WILL pass.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.2 Td (  6. After: reconnect, don't lecture. 'That was hard. I'm here.') Tj ET
endstream
endobj
